# Overflow & text containment

> Source canonique : `.agents/overflow.md`

GPUI does **not** wrap or clip text by default. `max_w` on a flex row is not enough.

## Must-do

- `min_w(px(0.0))` on flex-grow text columns inside capped parents
- `overflow_hidden()` on toast/bubble shells
- Multi-line body: split on `\n`, each line in `div().max_w(...)` (see `SupportView::render_message`)
- Single-line labels: `truncate()` or `line_clamp(1)`

## Centered modals

**Prefer adabraka `Dialog`** (see `.agents/ui-components.md`).

Legacy overlay **must** have:
- `max_h(px(...))` or `relative(0.85)` on the card
- scroll body: `flex_grow` + `min_h(0)` + `overflow_y_scroll`
- `flex_shrink_0` header + footer

Never stack chip rows + editor in an unbounded `flex_col` centered with `items_center`.

## Before shipping dynamic text

Ask: *longest realistic string?* (API error, path, UUID). Contain in the same PR.
